---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Operations and Scale"
  description="Operations leadership case study: datacenter-to-director progression, team scaling, P&L ownership, and measurable performance improvements."
  ogType="article"
>
  <article class="space-y-10">
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <p class="eyebrow">Case Study</p>
      <h1 class="section-title">Operations &amp; Scale</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Career progression at GCS Technologies from Datacenter Lead to Technical Support Manager to Director of Operations
        over a nine-year period.
      </p>
    </div>

    <section class="card space-y-4" data-reveal>
      <h2 class="font-mono text-2xl font-semibold">Leadership Arc</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-textMuted">
        <li>Managed a 30-person team and owned business-unit delivery quality.</li>
        <li>Directed P&amp;L execution and strategic initiatives tied to recurring growth.</li>
        <li>Exceeded revenue targets for seven consecutive quarters.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="card space-y-4 md:ml-8" data-reveal>
      <h2 class="font-mono text-2xl font-semibold">Operational Improvements</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-textMuted">
        <li>Built internal training programs that increased utilization from 73% to 86%.</li>
        <li>Implemented customer feedback loops that improved retention and service predictability.</li>
        <li>Standardized escalation and delivery processes for better reliability under load.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="card space-y-4 border-l-4 border-l-accent/40" data-reveal>
      <h2 class="font-mono text-2xl font-semibold">Foundation</h2>
      <p class="text-textMuted">
        Started on bare metal and progressed through each stack layer into architecture and executive operations, which
        now informs practical decision-making across security and AI systems work.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</MainLayout>
